There is a patch which might fix this problem.  See the list at:

    ftp://ftp.ips.cs.tu-bs.de/pub/local/softech/ddd/patches/
    ftp://ftp.th-darmstadt.de/pub/programming/tools/ddd/patches/
    ftp://ftp.gre.ac.uk/pub/tools/debuggers/ddd/patches/
    ftp://uiarchive.cso.uiuc.edu/pub/packages/ddd/patches/
    ftp://richb-pc.acc.qc.edu/pub/ddd/patches/

When using GCC 2.8.0, `ddd/VSLRead.o' must be generated without `-O'
flag.  Type `cd ddd; rm VSLRead.o; make CXXOPT=-DNDEBUG VSLRead.o' and
re-build DDD.


